xt-decoration: underline;">Chris Power</a>, Hadrian&#8217;s founder and CEO=
, is clear about the <strong>stakes</strong>: if the US loses military and =
space superiority this decade, totalitarian actors won&#8217;t just take co=
ntrol of the reserve currency and power on the home planet, they&#8217;ll s=
ettle the solar system.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We&#8217;re in a <strong>second Space R=
ace</strong>, one with astronomical stakes, and we&#8217;re at risk of losi=
ng because <strong>we can&#8217;t build like we used to</strong>. That&#821=
7;s what Hadrian wants to fix. Chris calls it the &#8220;anti-decline compa=
ny.&#8221; He wants to remind people that we can still build hard things in=
 the real world fast, like we did in the 1960s.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Part of t=
he reason Americans can&#8217;t build like we could in the &#8216;60s is th=
at we&#8217;re still relying on the same advanced manufacturing supply chai=
n we were back then, two generations (and a lot of excitement and optimism)=
 removed.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">So to reverse decline, Hadrian plans to transfo=
rm the legacy supply chain that powers <strong>space</strong> and <strong>d=
efense</strong> manufacturing today into one that is faster, cheaper, more =
reliable, and more transparent.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To do it, Chris has assem=
bled the <strong>Avengers</strong> &#8211; world-class software engineers, =
machinists, CAM programmers, operations leaders, and data scientists &#8211=
; to transform the faltering legacy space and defense industrial base in th=
e United States into a <strong>hyper efficient techno-industrial base. </st=
rong>He warned them that it was going to be hard and painful, and they all =
signed up.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The team is building <strong>precision machine=
 factories </strong>that automate the repetitive and mindless things that c=
an be automated and create high paying, meaningful work around the things t=
hat humans do best<strong>.</strong> At the meta level, it&#8217;s building=
 a machine that <strong>turns tribal knowledge into software, processes, an=
d jobs</strong>.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Importantly, unlike self-driving trucks, which=
 will automate tons of people out of jobs, <strong>machine shops literally =
cannot hire enough people to scale. </strong>To meet demand, there is no al=
ternative but to simultaneously automate and train a new generation of skil=
led workers.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If Hadrian is successful, <em>any</em> compa=
ny that relies on precision parts &#8211; starting with space and moving in=
to defense, medical devices, semiconductors, and energy &#8211; will be abl=
e to <strong>build 10x faster and for half the cost</strong> that they&#821=
7;re able to today. That means faster iteration and cheaper costs for advan=
ced rockets, satellites, jets, and hypersonics.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If that h=
appens, US Defense will gain the manufacturing overmatch they need to <stro=
ng>maintain peace through strength on earth and in space</strong>. The US w=
ill win Space Race II. The solar system will be free. It&#8217;s a big visi=
on.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But first things first, Hadrian needs to ship its tig=
htly-focused set of first parts &#8211; high-margin, high-precision aluminu=
m components for space companies &#8211; on-time and on-budget. It needs to=
 continue to hire world-class talent from the worlds of bits and atoms and =
get them to work together to turn <strong>tribal manufacturing knowledge</s=
trong> into scalable software and processes. <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.s=
ubstack.com/c/eJxFkMtuxCAMRb9m2E3EM4EFi276GxEBZwY1gQhMq_Try0wWlaxryw9d-XiH8=
